

to make the slideshows,
need to make a directory like:
assets/img/NAME

with photos ending in .jpg

then cd to assets/img/NAME
and run
../../../tmp/make_slideshow.sh 15
( see https://sermoa.wordpress.com/2010/04/05/a-quick-way-to-resize-images-in-linux/ for logic behind the resizing commands)
to make thumbnails and down-size the images

then look at an example index.html (e.g., personal/LA_2017/index.html)


and replace the filenames manually. MAKE SURE YOU ARE USING THE *_1024* FILES MADE BY make_slideshow.sh -- these will be roughly correct sizes for a browser.
finally, add the appropriate lines to personal/index.md to make the link to the slideshow.

